<section id="font-manager-add">
<title>Adding font families</title>

<p>Once you start up <app>Font Manager</app>, you can use it to manage your font collection. The default font directory is <code>~/.local/share/fonts</code>. More source directories (like <code>~/fonts/</code>) can be added in the <link xref="font-manager-preferences">Preferences Pane</link></p>

<p>Adding fonts to the collection can be done via </p>

<list>
  <item><p>Menu item <gui>+</gui> in the <gui>title bar</gui></p></item>
  <item><p>Drag and Drop to the <link xref="font-manager-fontlist">font list</link></p></item>
</list>

</section>
<section id="font-manager-remove">
<title>Removing fonts</title>

<p>To remove a font family, click the <gui>-</gui> button and select the fonts to remove in the list. This works only with fonts that have been installed through <app>Font Manager</app> (see <link xref="#font-manager-add">adding font families</link>) and/or reside in the default directory. </p>
</section>

